1.4.0 · [source](about:blank/src/std/net/udp.rs.html#308-310)

Sets the read timeout to the timeout specified.

If the value specified is [`None`](about:blank/option/enum.Option.html#variant.None "variant std::option::Option::None"), then [`read`](about:blank/io/trait.Read.html#tymethod.read "method std::io::Read::read") calls will block indefinitely. An [`Err`](about:blank/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Err "variant std::result::Result::Err") is returned if the zero [`Duration`](../time/struct.Duration.html "struct std::time::Duration") is passed to this method.

##### [§](#platform-specific-behavior)Platform-specific behavior

Platforms may return a different error code whenever a read times out as a result of setting this option. For example Unix typically returns an error of the kind [`WouldBlock`](about:blank/io/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.WouldBlock "variant std::io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock"), but Windows may return [`TimedOut`](about:blank/io/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.TimedOut "variant std::io::ErrorKind::TimedOut").

##### [§](#examples-8)Examples

```
use std::net::UdpSocket;

let socket = UdpSocket::bind("127.0.0.1:34254").expect("couldn't bind to address");
socket.set_read_timeout(None).expect("set_read_timeout call failed");
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::net::UdpSocket;%0A++++%0A++++let+socket+=+UdpSocket::bind(%22127.0.0.1:34254%22).expect(%22couldn%27t+bind+to+address%22);%0A++++socket.set_read_timeout(None).expect(%22set_read_timeout+call+failed%22);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

An [`Err`](about:blank/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Err "variant std::result::Result::Err") is returned if the zero [`Duration`](../time/struct.Duration.html "struct std::time::Duration") is passed to this method:

```
use std::io;
use std::net::UdpSocket;
use std::time::Duration;

let socket = UdpSocket::bind("127.0.0.1:34254").unwrap();
let result = socket.set_read_timeout(Some(Duration::new(0, 0)));
let err = result.unwrap_err();
assert_eq!(err.kind(), io::ErrorKind::InvalidInput)
```

